<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jor.26.19863>
        a               fabio:JournalArticle ;
        dc:creator      "Decaens, Thibaud" , "Annoyer, Philippe" , "Moulin, Nicolas" ;
        dc:date         "2017" ;
        dc:title        "Diversity of mantids (Dictyoptera: Mantodea) of Sangha-Mbaere Region, Central African Republic, with some ecological data and DNA barcoding" ;
        bibo:endPage    "141" ;
        bibo:issue      "2" ;
        bibo:journal    "Journal of Orthoptera Research" ;
        bibo:pubDate    "2017-11-24" ;
        bibo:startPage  "117" ;
        bibo:volume     "26" ;
        fabio:hasPart   <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.> .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Rarefaction curve of Mantodea from Sangha-Mbaere Region (black curve) with an extrapolation in a hypothetical situation where sampling effort would be doubled (dashed curve); grey area = confidence interval." , "Figure 10. Species richness in the three zones studied: Ndoki = Dzanga-Ndoki National Park zone; Sangha = Dzanga-Sangha Special Reserve zone; Mbaere = Rest of the Sangha-Mbaere Region; grey chart = observed number of species; dashed chart = estimated richness (ACE index) and associated standard deviation." , "Figure 12. Specific richness in the different vegetation strata; grey = observed richness; dashed chart = estimated richness (ACE index) and associated standard deviation." , "Figure 6. Specific richness of Mantodea collected with two main sampling methods; day capture (Day) and trapping with UV light at night (UV); grey chart = observed richness; dashed chart = estimated richness (ACE index) and associated standard deviation." , "Figure 7. Number of mantid species collected with the two main sampling methods: day capture (Day) and light trapping (UV)." , "Figure 13. Distribution of the species in the different vegetation strata." , "Figure 11. Number of collected specimens in the different vegetation strata; black = females; grey = males; white = nymphs." , "Figure 5. Number of mantid specimens collected with the two main sampling methods: day capture (Day) and trapping with UV lights at night (UV); black chart = females; grey chart = males; white chart = nymphs." , "Figure 8. Neighbor-joining tree of DNA barcodes (COI) obtained from BOLD 4.0. beta using the Kimura 2 parameter for distance model. Filters: sequence length> 200 bp." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169919" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169912" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169916" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169913" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169917" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169914" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169911" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169915" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/169918" .

